@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Angoes" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at least 8
colours.

                             How to play?

MAIN MENU

  When run, the game shows the main menu with the following buttons:

-About               -Displays the informations about 'Angoes'.

-Choose Your Colours -This button enters a menu where you can choose your
                      prefered colours and the game will use those colours.
                      The @{b}choosen@{ub} colours are 'pressed down'. To select
                      or unselect a colour, just click on it, this will
                      toggle it on or off. Note that you must choose at
                      least 4 different colours.

-Play!!              -To play the game.

GAMEPLAY

  To play, simply click on any angle (the "V" shaped thingies on the game
board), this will toggle its direction from left to right or from up to
down (or vice versa) depending on how it is placed. If the angle is part
of a series of 3 or more angles pointing in the same direction, all the
angles will be removed, and you will get points according to the number
of angles that were removed, as shown in the following table:

 3 angles:   1 point
 4 angles:  10 points
 5 angles:  40 points

  Note that as long as the angles point in the same direction, their
colours don't have to match, but the amount of points is multiplied by
5 if all the angles are of the same colour.

  As the angles are removed, the angles located over will fall in the
emptied spaces. If the fallen angles create series of 3 or more angles
pointing in the same direction, those angles will be removed and you
will get points accordingly.

  The game ends when it is no longer possible to make a series of at
least 3 angles.

  Angoes keeps the best score made since the game was run.

  You can abort a game at any time by clicking on the window's close
button, this will return the game to the main menu.

  Have fun!

@endnode

